The expected value of 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{n}\sim\Gamma(n,a)$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $na$
\end_inset

 and the variance is 
\begin_inset Formula $na^{2}$
\end_inset

.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $a=1/n$
\end_inset

 we therefore have 
\begin_inset Formula $E(Y_{n})=1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $V(Y_{n})=1/n$
\end_inset

.
 We need to prove that for any 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon>0$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P\left(\left|Y_{n}-1\right|>\varepsilon\right)\rightarrow0\quad\text{ as }n\rightarrow\infty.
\]

\end_inset

